rComments: Absolutely love this Professor. He is more concerned with helping students gain knowledge than he is with over-stressing them with difficult assignments. He requires a midterm which is fairly reflective of the course materials, a final, and 5 "pop-quizzes" throughout the semester which he openly prepares you for. Reading is crucial for success.

Le cours danthropologie politique est bien struturé et organisé. Le prof souhaite que les étudiants réussissent et il était prêt à adapter les exigences des travaux pour aider les étudiants à rendre un travail de qualité. Il est ouvert aux suggestions quant aux sujets parlés en classe et cest un cours interactif.

Scott Simon is a great prof. He is my favorite of all Anthropology department professors at Uottawa. He really wants us to do well. He adjusts the syllabus if we express concerns. He answers our questions and he is very available outside of class. He tries to make classes more interesting by trying different methods (videos, activities).

Class itself was unremarkable. He was clearly knowledgeable but based on the lack of contribution in class discussion he just couldn't seem to keep the class engaged. He provided no feedback on the final paper and defended this saying that he didn't believe that people read the comments, which is a pretty poor excuse.

This class was not what I thought it would be. The description did not match the course material in my opinion. There were soooo many readings I could not keep up with them and I feel that he did not convey the readings very well in his lectures, but he is helpful if you ask him.

Teaches directly from the textbook.  One of the FOUR BOOKS you have to buy is his own (I guess that's a smart way to increase sales, eh?). Fortunately, I was smart enough to photocopy the books.  Saved me $60.

A lot of my friends love him... he just didn't do it for me. He plays very strongly to his favorites and tends to pretend no one else is in the class. Unless you are his pet, prepare to feel like wallpaper.... not awful, just not as good as i was expecting from the hype.
Best Prof ever! He wants his students to do well and his classes are interesting. He is a real bleeding heart.
Scott Simon is the best prof at uottawa, hands down. He is not intimidating and he rewards students with good grades if they have worked hard.I would highly recommend his courses to anyone.

didn't really do it for me. A nice guy, very knowledgeable... but not that engaging. Didn't provide much feedback on assignments, class kind of drags by... wish he had put a little effort into engaging discussion with people other than his 3 favorites.

By far one of the best professors I had at Ottawa U.  He did talk alot about Taiwan, but he was still very nice and very helpful!  I took many courses with him, and I loved everyone.  Not to mention I got anywhere from an A- to an A+ in his classes!   Get to know him, and he will like you and you will do well!!!
Simon has very effective ways of teaching. If you are a lefty/idealist you will really like his classes. Once in a while he gets PMS but in general he is like the Buddha.
He's awesome! It's nice to finally see someone with experience in the field instead of just memorizing textbooks and overheads. Awesome class!
ENOUGH WITH THE TALK ON ASIA!!!   THERE ARE OTHER PLACES IN THE WORLD OTHER THEN ASIA!!!!
best teacher I`ve had so far at ottawa U, he`s almost too good to be teaching there.  Has travelled all over the world and he deals with issues most people are afraid to address.
Getting better.  Likes to talk about himself but is always willing to help.
